(11, 3, '2010-02-17 13:41:21', '2010-02-17 13:41:21', '<p>Day one and it certainly felt a bit like being a kid on my first day at school, but I had a pretty open mind as to who or what I may discover.  The day was full of interesting conversations, different objectives and hopes for what people may get from the experience.  There were numerous talks and workshops that helped position the content and develop relationships with the new alumni.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The talk that really stood out to me was delivered by Dr Bill Lancaster.  Bill helped me understand two things; 1) why my Mother still nags me – due to women holding the role of ‘policewoman’ in the family since the 1600’s, still apparent in my family! 2) The Bigg Market ethos and the reasons why us Geordies wear short sleeved shirts and mini skirts in the winter – all down to the prosperous times of ‘flashy lads and lasses’ from back in the shipyards and heavy industry era.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>I think the main thing that I observed that day was motivation for leadership and purpose.  All of the people I spoke to regarding purpose had a negative experience either in school or their career.  This has acted almost as a catalyst of extreme motivation to achieve something based on strong values and beliefs.  I was quite moved by the level of motivation and determination to really make a difference to the people’s lives they could affect.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>It has made me question, as to my own journey regarding what I am trying to achieve.   I have a clear direction of where I am going, but what I deem as ‘achievement’ is still a question I need to explore.  With the word ‘achievement’ like I found on the first day the meaning of words can be very different from person to person.</p>', 'Common Purpose day one: Plotting the Course', 'Day 1 and it certainly felt a bit like being a kid on my first day at school, but I had a pretty open mind as to who or what I may discover.', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'common-purpose-%e2%80%93-the-sage-%e2%80%93-day-1-%e2%80%93-plotting-the-course', '', '', '2010-10-21 13:25:14', '2010-10-21 13:25:14', '', 0, 'http://www.sherpabusinessconsultancy.com/wordpress/?p=11', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(608, 2, '2010-10-13 15:14:38', '2010-10-13 15:14:38', 'As businesses grow they can become dysfunctional and lose the focus and ability to execute the business plan. With an increased pressure for sales, improved products, services and market opportunities keep the business focussed on what makes money and the financial control to keep the business profitable.\r\n\r\nSherpa help the management team stay focussed on creating opportunities, closing deals, building the brand and delivering first class products and services, with strong control on processes and finance to ensure business growth.\r\n\r\nAn effective and well balanced management team is the cornerstone of a successful business, but more importantly to ensure the business can scale and cope with the growth. Sherpa takes business leaders through a self discovery process to indentify key strengths and create awareness of what the team needs to be successful. We look at skills gaps and profiling the right candidates to build the team.\r\n\r\nA strategy review allows the business to see where it is and build an action plan to reach its aspirations. A boardroom simulation allows the business to become sales led with a process improvement culture. \r\n\r\nBusinesses involved in finance raising often need key strengths to balance the team and gain traction.\r\n\r\n', 'Organisation Structure', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '132-revision-8', '', '', '2010-10-13 15:14:38', '2010-10-13 15:14:38', '', 132, 'http://www.sherpabusinessconsultancy.com/wordpress/business-consultancy/132-revision-8.html', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(252, 1, '2010-09-27 12:58:48', '2010-09-27 12:58:48', 'Sherpa Clinic is a one day workshop designed to diagnose any barriers to growth and identify potential opportunities in your business. Sherpa Clinic gives businesses the opportunity to have a comprehensive review of their current business strategy, operations and team. \r\n\r\nSherpa facilitate the workshop in a boardroom format, working with the business owner and management team to take stock of the fundamentals. Sherpa Clinic provides a holistic overview and analysis of key areas of the business including:\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Strategy</li> \r\n<li>Sales and customers</li> \r\n<li>Finance</li>\r\n<li>Operations</li> \r\n<li>People</li> \r\n</ul>\r\n\r\nSherpa Clinic provides third party objectivity and the ability to take a step back and make informed decisions on the current and future position of the business. It''s sometimes difficult to recognise when your business is not fulfilling its potential or how you are going to tackle it if you do. \r\n\r\nContact Sherpa on 0191 211 1995 to see how we can help you realise the potential in your business and provide you with a plan of action to achieve your vision.', 'Sherpa Clinic', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'sherpa-clinic', '', '', '2010-11-01 14:58:33', '2010-11-01 14:58:33', '', 0, 'http://www.sherpabusinessconsultancy.com/wordpress', 0, 'page', '', 0),
