(136, 1, '2010-09-24 12:50:29', '2010-09-24 12:50:29', 'A finance director is one of the most valuable assets to a profitable company. Good financial information informs business critical decisions and well managed financial controls are imperative to a healthy cash flow.  \r\n\r\nFor many entrepreneurs finance is not a key strength and can be a distraction from leading the business and bringing in sales. But having a senior financial professional who understands the business and adds value strategically as well as operationally is key to making the right decisions for the business.  \r\n\r\nHow clear are you on where the business is and what happens if targets are not met? A part time finance director can be a great advantage to an SME. An objective team member can improve decision making and challenge boardroom decisions to allow you to focus on priorities - winning business, leading the team and delivering great products and services.\r\n\r\nIf you are considering raising finance for your business, a finance director can add a lot of credibility and value to support you through the business planning, financial modelling, due diligence and pitching process. This allows you to stay focused the business and the execution of the plan.', 'Financial Support', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'financialsupport', '', '', '2010-10-27 13:55:17', '2010-10-27 13:55:17', '', 116, 'http://www.sherpabusinessconsultancy.com/wordpress/?page_id=136', 0, 'page', '', 0);
