(144, 1, '2010-09-24 12:52:56', '2010-09-24 12:52:56', 'A business mentor or coach helps you reach your goals and gives you motivation and encouragement to keep on track. One to one support adds value to your business by helping you to set goals, facilitate clear decision-making and achieve peak performance. The benefit of having someone else’s wealth of skills, experience and expertise helps you avoid pitfalls and recognise opportunities that you may not be aware of.  \r\n\r\nIf you feel you need to grow personally and develop or improve in some area, a mentor keeps you focused on your goals and helps you realise your potential. If you are starting out in business, it helps to have someone with more experience to share their knowledge and keep you on the right track. \r\n\r\nMany successful entrepreneurs and executives attribute their success to a business mentor or coach giving them support and guidance to achieve specific goals. The relationship between the entrepreneur and mentor involves a lot of trust from both sides, but the result of having someone with business experience to guide you through tough decisions and offer tactical support of how to improve your business is invaluable. ', ' Mentoring & Coaching', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'mentoring-coaching', '', '', '2010-11-01 09:35:38', '2010-11-01 09:35:38', '', 60, 'http://www.sherpabusinessconsultancy.com/wordpress/?page_id=144', 4, 'page', '', 0),
