(149, 1, '2010-09-24 12:53:38', '2010-09-24 12:53:38', 'Sherpa offers support throughout all stages of raising finance – preparing for investment, raising finance then coping and managing the growth. If you want to raise money for your business, Sherpa can help you through the process. \r\n\r\nIf you have no experience of raising finance there are a number of things you need to consider and prepare for that we can help you with:\r\n\r\n<strong>A compelling business plan:</strong> An investor level business plan is likely to be very different to the business plans you are familiar with. There is a great deal of work to be done in terms of getting your business in order, shaping the offer and financial projections.\r\n<strong>Finding the right funding or VC:</strong> It’s essential to research and select the right fund or investor for your business. This is determined by the size of investment, which industry and meeting the requirements of the investors.\r\n<strong>Term sheet:</strong> The business plan opens the debate with investors, the aim of these discussions is to get a term sheet. The term sheet is the investors offer and outlines the main terms of the deal including amount of investment, valuation and other terms and conditions\r\n<strong>Due diligence:</strong> Investors need key financial, legal and commercial information before committing to the finance. It’s a rigorous process but essential to reassure your investors of a sound offer.\r\n<strong>Post finance:</strong> A stage people do not always consider when the main focus is winning the money. Investors want transparent information and quality management reporting so they have visibility in the business. An interim finance director helps you develop robust systems and processes to make sure the money is managed and the team is accountable against the plan.\r\n\r\nSherpa act on a consultancy or interim basis to help you work with investors and VC’s. Raising finance is a lengthy and time consuming process and you can easily lose focus on the actual business. Having short term, expert support throughout the process helps you stay on track while staying focused on the business and the execution of the plan. We add value to help you recruit a senior team, find strategic partners and make early stage client introductions.\r\n', 'Investment & Venture Capital ', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'venturecapital', '', '', '2010-10-29 13:21:56', '2010-10-29 13:21:56', '', 60, 'http://www.sherpabusinessconsultancy.com/wordpress/?page_id=149', 3, 'page', '', 0),
