(153, 1, '2010-09-24 12:54:19', '2010-09-24 12:54:19', '<p>Non executive directors are extremely useful for any business that wants to grow or change. If you feel you may be in a comfort zone with business and would like to challenge the status quo, a non executive is a great solution. Because they are not wrapped up in the day-to-day running of the business, a non executive director can often see risks and opportunities the the executive management may overlook.</p> \r\n\r\n<p>Non executive directors are valuable during periods of change or growth in a business to bring specialised knowledge in a particular area. Sherpa have worked with businesses through times of corporate transition and can add significant value to your team if you are looking to:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Raise finance</li>\r\n<li>Build a sales strategy</li>\r\n<li>Improve operations</li>\r\n<li>Grow and motivate teams</li>\r\n</ul> \r\n\r\n<p>A non executive brings personal qualities and skills to the management team that may not currently exist. They can mediate if there are clashes with strong, difficult or opinionated personalities or add drive, innovation and dynamism if this is what the company is lacking. A non executive director can also bring a wealth of valuable contacts and high level connections in key target markets to make vital introductions. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Sherpa see things from a different perspective to the operational team and provide a vital strategic overview. Contact us for an initial meeting to find out where we can add value to your team and business.</p>\r\n', 'Non Executive Directors', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'non-executive-directors', '', '', '2010-11-01 16:39:45', '2010-11-01 16:39:45', '', 60, 'http://www.sherpabusinessconsultancy.com/wordpress/?page_id=153', 8, 'page', '', 0),
