(168, 1, '2010-09-24 13:05:41', '2010-09-24 13:05:41', 'Atlas Infrastructure Management provide virtualised desktop solutions to SME’s. Atlas approached Sherpa with a business concept based on their experience with a leading corporate cloud computing provider. \r\n\r\nSherpa provided interim management at the critical stages of early growth in sales and finance to support the management team, filling skills gaps until the business could afford a full time solution. Through Sherpa’s investor readiness programme, Atlas has successfully raised its first round of funding, with further angel investment and wider VC interest secured for the second round. \r\n\r\n<strong>Background:</strong> The founders of Atlas were looking to build a business using their experience in the corporate market to provide a solution to SME’s through a utility based pricing model. They needed to test the viability of the product and service in the market place and build a business case to take the product to market. \r\n\r\nThey also needed to raise finance across three stages to build the business infrastructure, get early traction in the market and build a management team. The team needed to be sure the project was going to be a success as they were leaving lucrative, well paid jobs in large corporate companies.\r\n\r\n<strong>Solution:</strong> When starting a new business, the lack of balance or ability to build a brand, close deals and manage a tight cash flow is daunting. Sherpa added value and balance to the team operationally as well as strategically to accelerate growth and mitigate risk at this difficult early stage.\r\n\r\n<strong>Commercialisation</strong>\r\nSherpa supported Atlas through the entire commercialisation process including market research and feasibility, building the business case, financial modelling to securing first clients. \r\n\r\n<strong>Interim Management</strong>\r\nActing in an interim capacity to the business, Sherpa added drive and motivation to the management team to give them the confidence to make the change. Sherpa provided the contacts, tenacity and flexibility to add value to the project from concept development to first sales. The process worked because of the development of the strategy and building the business case. The rapid growth was the ability of the team to execute the plan.\r\n\r\n<strong>Financial Modelling</strong>\r\nWith a capital high fronted the model investors need a robust plan to secure the high upfront cost of of funding. Attracting appropriate angel investment with the cultural fit and door opeing capability will be a further catalyst to rapid growth.\r\n\r\nContact Sherpa on <strong>0191 211 1995</strong> to arrange your free no obligation consultation. ', 'Atlas Infrastructure Management', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'atlas', '', '', '2010-11-01 12:03:44', '2010-11-01 12:03:44', '', 58, 'http://www.sherpabusinessconsultancy.com/wordpress/?page_id=168', 1, 'page', '', 0),
