(195, 1, '2010-09-20 13:47:37', '2010-09-20 13:47:37', '<div id="_mcePaste">Day 2 was a leadership facilitation where we worked with an ex-alumni. Throughout the exercise it struck me that leadership issues were all about people and the biggest issues were often based around leaders not facing their own demons or even more commonly, being too close to something to really understand how it was affecting them and they were affecting it.</div>\r\n<div>Often people are caught up so much in the doing that they don’t get the time to revisit some of the key strategic directions, such as where we are going, who are we at the moment and what we would like to be in future. It seems obvious that preventing is cheaper than curing, but without the openness and objectivity it takes longer to get there. Through digging at the base of the issues it therefore seemed imperative that the goals for the individual were not secondary to the goals of the organisation.</div>\r\n<div id="_mcePaste">In reflection, it made me look at my own short, medium and long term plans. Short term (the quick and the dirty)  review skills gaps,  look at marketing, identify who is best fit to help us, get a mentor. Medium term (where we are going) revisiting and adding to the action plan, with big enough milestones to make a difference and with small enough actions to have daily responsibility. Long term (sharing the vision) recommunicating the strategy of the business, whilst meeting and delivering the expectations of the team.</div>\r\n<div id="_mcePaste">I find it amazing how crucial time out of your own organisation is to meet with like-minded and diverse groups to help with your own development of how you see the world.</div>', 'Common Purpose Day 2 – Leadership Facilitation', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '18-revision-9', '', '', '2010-09-20 13:47:37', '2010-09-20 13:47:37', '', 18, 'http://www.sherpabusinessconsultancy.com/wordpress/?p=195', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
