(286, 1, '2010-10-04 08:33:56', '2010-10-04 08:33:56', 'Getting early traction can be difficult for start up businesses. Winning your first customers is a challenge, particularly with new products and services. Confidence and passion is natural for entrepreneurs and this can be very compelling when channeled into a sales pitch with the right support and coaching.\r\n\r\nIt’s important to have a clear strategy for sales, it’s very easy to lose track in the early stages with sales. Staying focused on what you want to be known for, the clients you want to work with and the projects you want to win is essential as you grow and define your brand.\r\n\r\nHaving the support of an experienced sales mentor is invaluable at this stage to help you define your strategy, process and target markets but more importantly to manage activity and progress so all of this happens. Our sales mentors and coaches provide you with a range tools and techniques to develop your and improve success in sales. ', 'Essential Early Sales', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'essentialearlysales', '', '', '2010-10-26 14:35:19', '2010-10-26 14:35:19', '', 109, 'http://www.sherpabusinessconsultancy.com/wordpress', 3, 'page', '', 0),
