(332, 2, '2010-10-06 08:38:35', '2010-10-06 08:38:35', 'If you have decided to go for the investment option, investor readiness is the key to success. \r\n\r\nJust like anyone making a major purchase, investors need reassurance of a sound investment. They require an excellent product, a unique service proposition, the ability to save their customers time or money, and the potential to generate significant revenue. On top of this investors are looking for a solid and experienced management team in charge of the business. \r\n\r\nSherpa help businesses become investor ready and support you during and after the process. We help you prepare for the implications, impact and liabilities on you and your business.  \r\n\r\nDepending on the stage you are at and the size of your team we can act either on a consultancy or interim basis. Sherpa can transfer vital skills to your team or join your management team on a short term basis to fast track the process and increase your chances for success. \r\n', 'Are You Investor Ready?', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'are-you-investor-ready', '', '', '2010-10-25 14:46:24', '2010-10-25 14:46:24', '', 113, 'http://www.sherpabusinessconsultancy.com/wordpress', 0, 'page', '', 0),
(333, 2, '2010-10-06 08:38:28', '2010-10-06 08:38:28', 'If you have decided to go for the investment option, investor readiness is the key to success. Just like anyone making a major purchase, investors need reassurance of a sound investment. \n\nThey require an excellent product, a unique service proposition, the ability to save their customers time or money, and the potential to generate significant revenue. On top of this investors are looking for a solid and experienced management team in charge of the business.\n\nSome of the key parts of the process you need to consider in preparing for investment: \n\nA compelling/winning business plan\nThe term sheet\nDue diligence – financial, legal, commercial \nClosing the investment round\nPost finance\n\n1.	Financial – detailed P&L and balance sheet; historical performance data; ensuring the current accounts are in order; there are no unaccounted liabilities; debtors and creditors are under control; systems are in place to deal with all management and compliance obligations; sound processes are in place for authorising payments; corporate governance standards, etc.\n\n2.	Legal – reviewing all current and relevant past contracts (commercial; employment); intellectual property protection (patents; trademarks); corporate structures (providing clarity and simplicity for incoming investors); shareholder agreements (terms and conditions that may impact incoming investors); supplier and customer agreements; trading terms and condition, etc.\n\n3.	Commercial – value proposition; business plans including future development roadmaps, new business initiatives, marketing strategies, sales/profit forecasts, HR structures, resource requirements, SWOT analyses; supplier/customer interviews to establish reputational bona fides and quality of the core value propositions; infrastructure audits; disaster recovery plans, etc.', 'Are You Investor Ready?', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '332-revision', '', '', '2010-10-06 08:38:28', '2010-10-06 08:38:28', '', 332, 'http://www.sherpabusinessconsultancy.com/wordpress/business-consultancy/332-revision.html', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
