(353, 2, '2010-10-06 08:52:20', '2010-10-06 08:52:20', 'Tough decisions are inevitable. Managing a business and leading a team present many challenges in key areas such as performance management, organisational change, operations and choices around strategic direction. It can be difficult to know what the best solution is and whether you are making the right decision.\r\n\r\nLeading a business can be a lonely place. When your team depends on you for final decisions on business critical issues, there are few people you can consult. Often these are highly sensitive or confidential situations that will impact the team or direction of the business.  \r\n  \r\nHaving the objectivity of a third party such as a non exec or a mentor helps tackle the thought process and give confidence in decision making. An impartial and experienced sounding board offers valuable support to move past tough obstacles and testing times.', 'Making Tough Decisions', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'making-tough-decisions', '', '', '2010-11-01 10:50:17', '2010-11-01 10:50:17', '', 116, 'http://www.sherpabusinessconsultancy.com/wordpress', 0, 'page', '', 0),
