(441, 2, '2010-10-08 11:43:17', '2010-10-08 11:43:17', 'Money is a major concern for start up businesses. There are many different schemes and sources of funding and finance to apply for at this stage of growth in a business. The problem is researching and navigating the many options and identifying the right one for you.\r\n\r\nMoney is available from various government departments and agencies nationally and locally to support start up businesses, innovation and enterprise. \r\n\r\nFunding should help you achieve your vision and push you in the direction you want to go in, not take you off into a different direction, purely because it fits the criteria. It needs to fit with you current plans and not take your attention away from the day to day basics of sales.\r\n\r\n\r\nTypes of available funding \r\n\r\nDirect grant\r\nThis is a cash award, which is usually given out for activities such as training, employment, export development, recruitment or capital investment projects. With a direct grant most schemes require the company involved usually putting up around 50 per cent of the cost.\r\n\r\nRepayable grant\r\nUnder this type of scheme cash funding is offered for a project with the intention that the sums are paid out of future revenues. However if unfortunately the project fails, the grant is written off.\r\n\r\nSoft loan\r\nA soft loan is a special type of grant where the terms and conditions of repayment are more generous (or softer) than they would be under normal finance circumstances. So, for example, the interest rate may be less, or there may be no interest to repay at all, and the repayment term could also be for a longer period.\r\n\r\nEquity finance\r\nWith equity finance a capital sum is injected into the business and the provider of the funds takes an equity share of the enterprise and (hopefully) when the value of the firm increases the stake can then be returned. However, unlike venture capitalists, the expectations and requirements of the providers of public funds are usually less demanding.\r\n', 'Start Up Funding ', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '124-revision-17', '', '', '2010-10-08 11:43:17', '2010-10-08 11:43:17', '', 124, 'http://www.sherpabusinessconsultancy.com/wordpress/business-consultancy/124-revision-17.html', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
