(473, 2, '2010-10-08 14:24:58', '2010-10-08 14:24:58', 'Money is a major concern for start up businesses. There are many different schemes and sources of funding and finance to apply for at this stage of growth in a business. \r\n\r\nFunding is available from various government departments and agencies nationally and locally to support start up businesses, innovation and enterprise. The problem is researching and navigating the many options and identifying the right one for you.\r\n\r\nFunding should fit with your business model and current plans, be careful not to tailor your business around funding schemes and criteria as this can often lead to a loss of direction. \r\n\r\nMost grants and funding are low risk with flexible terms, but some require an equity share in the business. Sherpa can help you seek out the best schemes for your business, prepare you for what is required and support you though the application process. ', 'Start Up Funding ', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '124-revision-29', '', '', '2010-10-08 14:24:58', '2010-10-08 14:24:58', '', 124, 'http://www.sherpabusinessconsultancy.com/wordpress/business-consultancy/124-revision-29.html', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(474, 2, '2010-10-06 15:42:11', '2010-10-06 15:42:11', 'The business plan is the first step, but making sure you deliver it is another matter. The reality of how you will meet your objectives \r\n\r\nIt’s essential that you plan, track and manage progress at this early stage of business growth. Short term, tactical goals are key to measuring progress and success. ', 'Making It Happen', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '126-revision-10', '', '', '2010-10-06 15:42:11', '2010-10-06 15:42:11', '', 126, 'http://www.sherpabusinessconsultancy.com/wordpress/business-consultancy/126-revision-10.html', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
