(485, 2, '2010-10-12 12:44:49', '2010-10-12 12:44:49', ' \r\nAtlas Infrastructure Management provide virtualised desktop solutions to SME''s. \r\n\r\nAtlas approached Sherpa with a business concept based on their experience with a leading corporate cloud computing provider. The founders of Atlas were looking to build a business using their experience in the corporate market to provide a solution to SME''s through a utility based pricing model. \r\n\r\nAtlas needed to test the viability of the product and service in the market place and build a business case to take the product to market.\r\n\r\nThey also needed to raise finance across three stages to build the business infrastructure, get early traction in the market and build a management team.\r\n\r\nAtlas has successfully raised its first round of funding, with further angel investment and wider VC interest secured for the second round through Sherpa''s investor readiness consultancy programme. \r\n\r\nSherpa then provided interim management at the critical stages of early growth in sales and finance to support the management team, filling skills gaps until the business could afford a full time solution.', 'Atlas Infrastructure Management', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '168-revision-6', '', '', '2010-10-12 12:44:49', '2010-10-12 12:44:49', '', 168, 'http://www.sherpabusinessconsultancy.com/wordpress/business-consultancy/168-revision-6.html', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
