(607, 2, '2010-10-18 12:46:54', '2010-10-18 12:46:54', 'Leading a business can be a difficult and lonely place. With a dynamic market place and team, comes challenge and need for common purpose.  Facing your demons can be a time lesser people would hope a problem would go away.  Having the objectivity of a third party such as a Non Exec or a mentor, helps to keep on the path and have the support to move past tough obstacles.\r\n \r\nPerformance management, restructures leading change are key times when action is needed fast to pull the team into a positive and proactive direction. ', 'Making Tough Decisions', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '353-revision-3', '', '', '2010-10-18 12:46:54', '2010-10-18 12:46:54', '', 353, 'http://www.sherpabusinessconsultancy.com/wordpress/business-consultancy/353-revision-3.html', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(610, 2, '2010-10-21 10:33:22', '2010-10-21 10:33:22', 'As businesses grow they can become dysfunctional and lose the focus and ability to execute the business plan. Sherpa help the management team stay focussed on creating opportunities, closing deals, building the brand and delivering first class products and services, with strong control on processes and finance to ensure business growth.\r\n\r\nAn effective and well balanced management team is the cornerstone of a successful business, but more importantly to ensure the business can scale and cope with the growth. Sherpa takes business leaders through a self discovery process to indentify key strengths and create awareness of what the team needs to be successful. We look at skills gaps and profile the right candidates to build the team.\r\n\r\nA strategy review allows you to see where the business is and build an action plan to reach your aspirations. It can also be very valuable to have a third party presence in board meetings to help challenge decisions and drive activity. \r\n\r\n', 'Organisation Structure', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '132-revision-9', '', '', '2010-10-21 10:33:22', '2010-10-21 10:33:22', '', 132, 'http://www.sherpabusinessconsultancy.com/wordpress/business-consultancy/132-revision-9.html', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(611, 2, '2010-10-21 10:42:04', '2010-10-21 10:42:04', 'Entrepreneurs grow businesses with natural enthusiasm, desire and energy. With increasing demands on time, it can be difficult to prioritise and delegate away from something you are so close to. \n\nThere are tough questions to answer and decisions to be made to see where you add the most value and what the business needs to move up a gear. A growing business with an increasing head count brings new levels of complexity and internal challenges. Third party objectivity can help you take a step back from the day to day emails, administrative and staff issues to see the areas of the business that other people are better placed to solve problems and create solutions, allowing the business to blossom.\n\nSherpa works with the management team and the business leader to define what they need to be and what they need to focus on to drive and manage the business. Mentoring and coaching brings clarity to the team and the individual to deliver results and brings a culture of empowerment and ownership.\n\nUnderstanding and keeping a transformational role allows the entrepreneur to add value, delegate and recruit according to what the business needs to be successful. When you start a business you have to do everything the business needs, when you are a leader you have be everything the business needs.\n', 'Manage Your Time ', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '130-autosave', '', '', '2010-10-21 10:42:04', '2010-10-21 10:42:04', '', 130, 'http://www.sherpabusinessconsultancy.com/wordpress/business-consultancy/130-autosave.html', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
