(618, 2, '2010-10-21 11:27:01', '2010-10-21 11:27:01', 'Case Study\r\n\r\nSherpa were approached by a leading third sector organisation seeking strategic guidance as they entered a period of economic uncertainty. \r\n\r\nThe organisation embarked on a development project with Sherpa, building a cohesive action plan to deal with a reduced budget and a commitment to providing adequate service provision to vulnerable users.\r\n\r\nBackground\r\n\r\nThe management team had identified a need for change due to impending budgetary cuts and were looking to create greater accountability through more streamlined business processes.\r\n\r\nThey also recognized the need to restructure the management team and to return to a focus on ‘core business’ to ensure that the services provided to their clients were not impacted by restricted finances.\r\n\r\nThe Solution\r\n\r\nA new management structure allowed the business to focus on what the organisation was originally created to provide. With greater control, the business was in a strong position to deal with financial issues as they arose. Reconfiguring the financial structure meant that the business could strategically plan to cope with budget cuts, and the outsourcing of non-service related roles to specialist providers created greater accountability and a return to core business.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n', 'Third sector', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '272-revision-6', '', '', '2010-10-21 11:27:01', '2010-10-21 11:27:01', '', 272, 'http://www.sherpabusinessconsultancy.com/wordpress/business-consultancy/272-revision-6.html', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
