(631, 1, '2010-10-13 16:53:59', '2010-10-13 16:53:59', 'This year I was again priveledged to be guest at <a href="http://www.gamelab.es/">Gamelab 2010</a> in the Spanish city of Gijón.\r\n\r\nGamelab is now in its sixth year and is going from strength to strength thanks to the hard work of conference producer Ivan Fernandez Lobo. Gamelab is the biggest event of its kind for the games and interactive industry in Spain. Its aim is to bring the Spanish games development community together to share knowledge and inspire new ideas. \r\n\r\nThe conference attracts speakers from the international industry not just Spain, and this year there were definitely more familiar faces from the international industry on the line up including Martin De Ronde (OneBigGame), Jørgen Tharaldsen (Funcom), Malte Behrmann (EGDF) and Nils Holger Henning (Bigpoint) who had jetted across from Newcastle following a slot at the GameHorizon Conference. \r\n\r\nOther familiar faces included Fred Hasson and Phil Elliott from media partner <a href="http://www.gamesindustry.biz/">gamesindustry.biz</a>. Phil was there to cover the conference and get a feel for the Spanish industry and what the issues and opportunities are. For more information on Gamelab 2010 see Ivan''s <a href="http://www.gamesindustry.biz/articles/gamelabs-ivan-fernandez-lobo-interview">interview</a>.\r\n\r\nThere were many other interesting speakers and talks including success on a low budget from Doodle Jump''s Igor Pusenjack (CEO LimaSky). \r\n\r\nConference high points: incredible VIP dinner and opportunity to practice my Spanish.\r\nConference low points: only one. I did not realise there was English translation until day two!\r\n\r\n', 'Gamelab 2010', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '39-revision-28', '', '', '2010-10-13 16:53:59', '2010-10-13 16:53:59', '', 39, 'http://www.sherpabusinessconsultancy.com/wordpress/business-consultancy/39-revision-28.html', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
