(646, 2, '2010-10-21 15:24:48', '2010-10-21 15:24:48', 'Entrepreneurs in start up businesses will be more than familiar with performing more than one role. As managing director there is a good chance you are also in charge of finance, operations, sales and delivery, working very long hours! This is typical at this stage of business but it’s important to recognise that this is not a long term solution without a support network or strategy for growth. \n\nYou need to ensure that during this start up phase, although you are filling multiple functions, that roles and responsibilities still need to be clarified. It’s not the ideal situation but individuals still need to perform to the best of their ability so performance should be monitored and accountability assigned. \n\nAt the same time it’s essential to plan for growth. By identifying these roles and responsibilities at an early stage, you can identify who and when your next critical hire will be. What is your team going to look like in one, two, three years time? This also helps identify what you can outsource and leverage externally.\n\nFinally, by building a strategic network around the business, you may be able to plug vital skills without hiring. There are many orgnisations and networks that you can leverage by being tactical.\n\nSherpa can work with you to identify a growth plan around your business to balance\n', 'Building Your Team', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '414-autosave', '', '', '2010-10-21 15:24:48', '2010-10-21 15:24:48', '', 414, 'http://www.sherpabusinessconsultancy.com/wordpress/business-consultancy/414-autosave.html', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(647, 2, '2010-10-21 15:16:36', '2010-10-21 15:16:36', 'Start up businesses will be more than familiar with performing more than one role. As managing director there is a good chance you are also in charge of finance, operations, sales and delivery, working very long hours!\r\n\r\nThis is typical at this stage of business but it’s important to recognise that this is not a long term solution without a support network or strategy for growth.  \r\n\r\nYou need to ensure that during this start up phase, although you are filling multiple functions, that roles and responsibilities still need to be clarified. This is so performance can be monitored and accountability can be assigned. It’s not the ideal situation but individuals still need to perform to the best of their ability.\r\n\r\nAt the same time it’s essential to plan for growth. By identifying these roles and responsibilities at an early stage, you can identify who and when your next critical hire will be. What is your team going to look like in one, two, three years time? It also helps identify what you can outsource and leverage externally.\r\n\r\nFinally, by building a strategic network around the business, you may be able to plug vital skills without hiring. There are many orgnisations and networks that you can leverage by being tactical.\r\n\r\nSherpa can work with you to identify a growth plan around your business and team, balancing \r\n', 'Building Your Team', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '414-revision-9', '', '', '2010-10-21 15:16:36', '2010-10-21 15:16:36', '', 414, 'http://www.sherpabusinessconsultancy.com/wordpress/business-consultancy/414-revision-9.html', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
