(662, 2, '2010-10-25 13:25:58', '2010-10-25 13:25:58', 'It’s essential to keep control and focus on your sales strategy and process. Are you reaching the markets you want to be working in and the clients you want to be working with? Are you winning the right size and type of project? \n\nOften you get so involved in winning and delivering, it is very easy to lose focus and the direction you initially set out in. Reviewing essential basics by redesigning and revisiting your sales strategy brings this focus back and should make things much clearer and ultimately satisfying for everyone.\n\nWho is your ideal client and what do you want to be known for? Are you the type of business you set out to be? Maybe your sales are great but profitability is a concern. If you have built a great reputation for your business but are not getting the reward for it, it could be time to review your pricing strategy and be paid what you are worth. \n\nObjectivity from a sales expert is a great way to achieve this focus. A sales coach or mentor can help you and your team define your strategy and address all of these questions. They work with you to review your current situation and plan the way forward, help you exploit your strengths and address any areas that need development.\n', 'Improve Sales and Profit ', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '335-autosave', '', '', '2010-10-25 13:25:58', '2010-10-25 13:25:58', '', 335, 'http://www.sherpabusinessconsultancy.com/wordpress/business-consultancy/335-autosave.html', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
