(705, 2, '2010-10-21 16:04:38', '2010-10-21 16:04:38', 'Entrepreneurs in start up businesses will be more than familiar with performing more than one role. As managing director there is a good chance you are also in charge of finance, operations, sales and delivery, working very long hours! This is typical at this stage of business but it’s important to recognise that this is not a long term solution without a support network or strategy for growth. \r\n\r\nYou need to ensure that during this start up phase, although you are filling multiple functions, that roles and responsibilities still need to be clarified. It’s not the ideal situation but individuals still need to perform to the best of their ability so performance should be monitored and accountability assigned. \r\n\r\nAt the same time it’s essential to plan for growth. By identifying these roles and responsibilities at an early stage, you can identify who and when your next critical hire will be. What is your team going to look like in one, two, three years time? This also helps identify what you can outsource and leverage externally. By building a strategic network around the business, you may be able to plug vital skills without hiring. There are many organisations and networks that you can leverage by being tactical.\r\n\r\nSherpa can work with you to develop your team, the roles and responsibilities and identify a plan of how to scale the team with business growth.\r\n', 'Building Your Team', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '414-revision-17', '', '', '2010-10-21 16:04:38', '2010-10-21 16:04:38', '', 414, 'http://www.sherpabusinessconsultancy.com/wordpress/business-consultancy/414-revision-17.html', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(706, 2, '2010-10-11 15:08:18', '2010-10-11 15:08:18', 'Money is a major concern for start up businesses. There are many different schemes and sources of funding and finance to apply for at this stage of growth in a business. \r\n\r\nFunding is available from various government departments and agencies nationally and locally to support start up businesses, innovation and enterprise. The problem is researching and navigating the many options and identifying the right one for you.\r\n\r\nFunding should fit with your business model and current plans, be careful not to tailor your business around funding schemes and criteria as this can often lead to a loss of direction. \r\n\r\nMost grants and funding are low risk with flexible terms, but some require an equity share in the business. Sherpa can help you seek out the best schemes for your business, prepare you for what is required and support you though the application process. ', 'Start Up Funding ', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '124-revision-30', '', '', '2010-10-11 15:08:18', '2010-10-11 15:08:18', '', 124, 'http://www.sherpabusinessconsultancy.com/wordpress/business-consultancy/124-revision-30.html', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
