(756, 2, '2010-10-27 15:58:20', '2010-10-27 15:58:20', 'Some people are leaders, some are managers and the lucky few are both. When starting up as an entrepreneur the focus is growing yourself and your business. Once you have built the business and your team, the focus needs to shift towards growing and leading others, to realise the business potential.\r\n\r\nAs a leader you set the vision, values, culture and direction of the business. As a manager you take a proactive approach towards the day to day operations, resources and execution of your company strategy. How do you want to be perceived by your team, clients and peers? \r\n\r\nLeadership styles vary depending on what comes naturally or what the situation requires. Not everyone is a born leader, but you can take control and become the leader you need to be. Maintaining the vision and strategy whilst managing a team effectively is difficult, you need an effective management structure and team around you. Personally it requires focus and motivation as the business grows and presents more challenges. \r\n\r\nSherpa are experienced in leadership and management development. With the right development leaders can be highly effective. A business coach is a vital tool to help you stay focused and motivated. \r\n', 'Take control', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '351-revision-3', '', '', '2010-10-27 15:58:20', '2010-10-27 15:58:20', '', 351, 'http://www.sherpabusinessconsultancy.com/wordpress/business-consultancy/351-revision-3.html', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
