(776, 2, '2010-10-25 14:47:04', '2010-10-25 14:47:04', 'Sherpa offers support throughout all stages of raising finance – preparing for investment, raising finance then coping and managing the growth. \r\n\r\nDetermine your requirements\r\nSo you have made the decision that you need to raise money, but there are many other things to consider which Sherpa can help you with such as recruitment of senior team, strategic partners and early stage client introductions.\r\n\r\nBusiness plan\r\nThere is also a great deal of work to be on at this stage in creating a winning business plan.  Getting your business in order, shaping the offer, financials.\r\n\r\nVC support\r\nFinding the right funding or VC, size of investment, which industry, meeting their requirements. \r\n\r\nPost finance\r\nA stage people do not always acknowledge when the main focus is winning the money. \r\n\r\n\r\nSome of the key parts of the process you need to consider in preparing for investment:\r\n\r\nA compelling/winning business plan\r\nThe term sheet\r\nDue diligence – financial, legal, commercial\r\nClosing the investment round\r\nPost finance\r\n\r\n1.	Financial – detailed P&L and balance sheet; historical performance data; ensuring the current accounts are in order; there are no unaccounted liabilities; debtors and creditors are under control; systems are in place to deal with all management and compliance obligations; sound processes are in place for authorising payments; corporate governance standards, etc.\r\n\r\n3.	Commercial – value proposition; business plans including future development roadmaps, new business initiatives, marketing strategies, sales/profit forecasts, HR structures, resource requirements, SWOT analyses; supplier/customer interviews to establish reputational bona fides and quality of the core value propositions; infrastructure audits; disaster recovery plans, etc.\r\n', 'Investment & Venture Capital ', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '149-revision-15', '', '', '2010-10-25 14:47:04', '2010-10-25 14:47:04', '', 149, 'http://www.sherpabusinessconsultancy.com/wordpress/business-consultancy/149-revision-15.html', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
