(836, 2, '2010-10-27 16:10:35', '2010-10-27 16:10:35', 'Some people are leaders, some are managers and the lucky few are both. When starting up as an entrepreneur the focus is growing yourself and your business. Once you have built the business and your team, the focus needs to shift towards growing and leading others, to realise the business potential.\r\n\r\nAs a leader you set the vision, values, culture and direction of the business. As a manager you take a proactive approach towards the execution of the strategy and control the resources to achieve it. How do you want to be perceived by your team, clients and peers? \r\n\r\nLeadership styles vary depending on what comes naturally or what the situation requires. Not everyone is a born leader, but you can take control and become the leader you need to be. Maintaining the vision and strategy whilst managing a team effectively is difficult, you need an effective management structure and team around you. Personally it requires focus and motivation as the business grows and presents more challenges. \r\n\r\nSherpa are experienced in leadership and management development. With the right development leaders can be highly effective. A business coach is a vital tool to help you stay focused and motivated. \r\n', 'Take control', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '351-revision-9', '', '', '2010-10-27 16:10:35', '2010-10-27 16:10:35', '', 351, 'http://www.sherpabusinessconsultancy.com/wordpress/business-consultancy/351-revision-9.html', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(837, 2, '2010-10-21 13:26:47', '2010-10-21 13:26:47', '<p>This year I was again priveledged to be guest at <a href="http://www.gamelab.es/">Gamelab 2010</a> in the Spanish city of Gijón.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Gamelab is now in its sixth year and is going from strength to strength thanks to the hard work of conference producer Ivan Fernandez Lobo. Gamelab is the biggest event of its kind for the games and interactive industry in Spain. Its aim is to bring the Spanish games development community together to share knowledge and inspire new ideas. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>The conference attracts speakers from the international industry not just Spain, and this year there were definitely more familiar faces from the international industry on the line up including Martin De Ronde (OneBigGame), Jørgen Tharaldsen (Funcom), Malte Behrmann (EGDF) and Nils Holger Henning (Bigpoint) who had jetted across from Newcastle following a slot at the GameHorizon Conference. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Other familiar faces included Fred Hasson and Phil Elliott from media partner <a href="http://www.gamesindustry.biz/">gamesindustry.biz</a>. Phil was there to cover the conference and get a feel for the Spanish industry and what the issues and opportunities are. For more information on Gamelab 2010 see Ivan''s <a href="http://www.gamesindustry.biz/articles/gamelabs-ivan-fernandez-lobo-interview">interview</a>.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>There were many other interesting speakers and talks including success on a low budget from Doodle Jump''s Igor Pusenjack (CEO LimaSky). </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Conference high points: incredible VIP dinner and opportunity to practice my Spanish.<br/>\r\nConference low points: only one. I did not realise there was English translation until day two!</p>\r\n\r\n', 'Gamelab 2010', 'This year I was again privileged to be guest at Gamelab 2010 in the Spanish city of Gijón.', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '39-revision-30', '', '', '2010-10-21 13:26:47', '2010-10-21 13:26:47', '', 39, 'http://www.sherpabusinessconsultancy.com/wordpress/business-consultancy/39-revision-30.html', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
