(850, 1, '2010-10-28 14:42:52', '2010-10-28 14:42:52', 'A business mentor or coach helps you reach your goals and gives you motivation and encouragement to keep on track. One to one support adds value to your business by helping you to set goals, facilitate clear decision-making and achieve peak performance. \r\n\r\nIf you are starting out in business, it helps to have someone with more experience to share their knowledge and keep you on the right track. Maybe you have a great idea for a business but needs a bit of guidance to turn it into a successful and profitable venture. Or maybe you have been in business for a while and feel you need to grow personally and develop or improve in some area.\r\n\r\nMany successful entrepreneurs and executives attribute their success to a business mentor or coach giving them support and guidance to achieve specific goals.\r\n\r\nTop athletes and sports people could not achieve the level of success or results without a coach so why would it be any different in business. \r\n\r\nThe relationship between the entrepreneur and mentor involves a lot of trust from both sides, but the result of having someone with business experience to guide you through tough decisions and offer tactical support of how to improve your business, is invaluable\r\n\r\nIt’s a two-way communication process to share their wealth of skills, experience and expertise with those hungry for knowledge and guidance.', ' Mentoring & Coaching', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '144-revision-17', '', '', '2010-10-28 14:42:52', '2010-10-28 14:42:52', '', 144, 'http://www.sherpabusinessconsultancy.com/wordpress/business-consultancy/144-revision-17.html', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(903, 2, '2010-10-29 15:51:54', '2010-10-29 15:51:54', 'A business mentor or coach helps you reach your goals and gives you motivation and encouragement to keep on track. One to one support adds value to your business by helping you to set goals, facilitate clear decision-making and achieve peak performance. The benefit of having someone else’s wealth of skills, experience and expertise helps you avoid pitfalls and recognise opportunities that you may not be aware of.  \r\n\r\nIf you feel you need to grow personally and develop or improve in some area, a mentor keeps you focused on your goals and helps you realise your potential. If you are starting out in business, it helps to have someone with more experience to share their knowledge and keep you on the right track. \r\n\r\nMany successful entrepreneurs and executives attribute their success to a business mentor or coach giving them support and guidance to achieve specific goals. The relationship between the entrepreneur and mentor involves a lot of trust from both sides, but the result of having someone with business experience to guide you through tough decisions and offer tactical support of how to improve your business is invaluable. ', ' Mentoring & Coaching', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '144-revision-19', '', '', '2010-10-29 15:51:54', '2010-10-29 15:51:54', '', 144, 'http://www.sherpabusinessconsultancy.com/wordpress/business-consultancy/144-revision-19.html', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(851, 1, '2010-10-28 14:17:37', '2010-10-28 14:17:37', 'Sherpa can provide experienced interim managers in key areas such as finance, sales, operations or management, to provide hands on, specialist support through periods of growth or change in your business. \r\n\r\nA fixed term partnership with an interim manager can strengthen your team by transferring essential skills and experience. We can help embed change, manage teams and make introductions into people who will add value to your business.', 'Interim Management', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '146-revision-7', '', '', '2010-10-28 14:17:37', '2010-10-28 14:17:37', '', 146, 'http://www.sherpabusinessconsultancy.com/wordpress/business-consultancy/146-revision-7.html', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(852, 1, '2010-10-28 14:18:42', '2010-10-28 14:18:42', 'An independent strategic review of your business help identify key issues or opportunities in your business. Sherpa work with you to identify the growth potential and bain your business and provide a road map of how to get there. provides an objective perspective to\r\n\r\nSherpa help define your business objectives, vision and mission to clarify your long-term direction and overall purpose and aspirations. We help you to create an action plan and implement your vision. \r\n\r\n', 'Strategic Review', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '142-revision-19', '', '', '2010-10-28 14:18:42', '2010-10-28 14:18:42', '', 142, 'http://www.sherpabusinessconsultancy.com/wordpress/business-consultancy/142-revision-19.html', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(853, 1, '2010-10-28 15:22:51', '2010-10-28 15:22:51', 'A robust sales strategy and process is essential for successful businesses. Sherpa provide a number of solutions to focus your sales strategy to maximise profit margins and growth. We get back to the basics to answer the vital questions of where you want to be, what are your core strengths and who are your ideal clients? This information is essential to shape your sales strategy. We will then provide you with an action plan to ensure you stay on track and reach your goals. Some of the specific areas sales development services include:\r\n\r\n<strong>Sales review:</strong> a holistic overview of your current sales situation – strengths, successes, weaknesses and failures. Where do you want to be? Who do you want to work with? What do you want to be famous for? \r\n<strong>Sales process:</strong> breaking down the process, making it targeted, manageable and achievable. Who is involved? How much time do you spend on sales? \r\n<strong>Channels to market:</strong> are you reaching your market potential? Sherpa help you define new markets \r\n<strong>Sales techniques:</strong> tools and techniques to improve your selling skills. Pitching, persuasion, negotiation and deal making.\r\n\r\n', ' Sales Development', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '151-revision-19', '', '', '2010-10-28 15:22:51', '2010-10-28 15:22:51', '', 151, 'http://www.sherpabusinessconsultancy.com/wordpress/business-consultancy/151-revision-19.html', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
