(987, 2, '2010-11-01 16:02:32', '2010-11-01 16:02:32', 'Non executive directors are extremely useful for any business that wants to grow or change. If you feel you may be in a comfort zone with business and would like to challenge the status quo, a non executive is a great solution. Because they are not wrapped up in the day-to-day running of the business, a non executive director can often see risks and opportunities the the executive management may overlook. \r\n\r\nNon executive directors are valuable during periods of change or growth in a business to bring specialised knowledge in a particular area. Sherpa have worked with businesses through times of corporate transition such as funding cuts, raising finances  uch as:\r\nsales\r\nfinance\r\noperations\r\n\r\nA non executive brings personal qualities and skills to the management team that may not currently exist. They can mediate if there are clashes with strong, difficult or opinionated personalities or add drive, innovation and dynamism if this is what the company is lacking. A non executive director can also bring a wealth of valuable contacts and high level connections in key target markets to make vital introductions. \r\n\r\nSherpa''s non executive directors see things from a different perspective to the operational team and provide a vital strategic overview.\r\n', 'Non Executive Directors', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '153-revision-10', '', '', '2010-11-01 16:02:32', '2010-11-01 16:02:32', '', 153, 'http://www.sherpabusinessconsultancy.com/wordpress/business-consultancy/153-revision-10.html', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(859, 2, '2010-10-29 10:45:12', '2010-10-29 10:45:12', 'Sherpa offers support throughout all stages of raising finance – preparing for investment, raising finance then coping and managing the growth. If you want to raise money for your business, Sherpa can help you through the process. If you have no experience of raising finance there are a number of things you need to consider and prepare for.\r\n\r\nA compelling business plan:  An investor level business plan is likely to be very different to the business plans you are familiar with. There is a great deal of work to be done in terms of getting your business in order, shaping the offer and financial projections.\r\nFinding the right funding or VC: It’s essential to research and select the right fund or investor for your business. This is determined by the size of investment, which industry and meeting the requirements of the investors.\r\nDue diligence: Investors need key financial, legal and commercial information before committing to the finance. It’s a rigorous process but essential to reassure your investors of a sound offer.\r\nTerm sheet: agreeing the principles of the deal – amount of investment, valuation and other terms and conditions\r\nPost finance: A stage people do not always consider when the main focus is winning the money. Investors want transparent information and quality management reporting so they have visibility in the business. An interim finance director helps you develop robust systems and processes to make sure the money is managed and the team is accountable against the plan.\r\n\r\nSherpa act on a consultancy or interim basis to help you work with investors and VC’s. Raising finance is lengthy and time consuming process and you can easily lose focus on the actual business. Having short term, expert support throughout the process helps you stay on track while staying focused on the business and the execution of the plan. We add value to help you recruit a senior team, find strategic partners and make early stage client introductions.\r\n', 'Investment & Venture Capital ', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '149-revision-39', '', '', '2010-10-29 10:45:12', '2010-10-29 10:45:12', '', 149, 'http://www.sherpabusinessconsultancy.com/wordpress/business-consultancy/149-revision-39.html', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
