(912, 2, '2010-10-27 14:47:07', '2010-10-27 14:47:07', 'Leading a business can be a lonely place. With ever changing internal and external conditions, prioritising your time spent in the business and on the business is challenging.\r\n\r\nTough decisions are inevitable. Managing a business and leading a team presents many challenges in key areas such as performance management, organisational change, operations and choices around strategic direction. It can be difficult to know what the best solution is and whether you are making the right decision.\r\n\r\nHaving the objectivity of a third party such as a non exec or a mentor helps tackle the thought process and give confidence in decision making. An impartial and experienced sounding board offers valuable support to move past tough obstacles and testing times.\r\n', 'Making Tough Decisions', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '353-revision-6', '', '', '2010-10-27 14:47:07', '2010-10-27 14:47:07', '', 353, 'http://www.sherpabusinessconsultancy.com/wordpress/business-consultancy/353-revision-6.html', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
