(916, 2, '2010-11-01 10:20:15', '2010-11-01 10:20:15', 'Tough decisions are inevitable. Managing a business and leading a team present many challenges in key areas such as performance management, organisational change, operations and choices around strategic direction. It can be difficult to know what the best solution is and whether you are making the right decision.\r\n\r\nLeading a business can be a lonely place. When your team depends on you for final decisions on business critical issues, there are few people you can consult. Often these are highly sensitive or confidential situations that will impact the team or direction of the business.  \r\n  \r\nHaving the objectivity of a third party such as a non exec or a mentor helps tackle the thought process and give confidence in decision making. An impartial and experienced sounding board offers valuable support to move past tough obstacles and testing times.', 'Making Tough Decisions', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '353-revision-9', '', '', '2010-11-01 10:20:15', '2010-11-01 10:20:15', '', 353, 'http://www.sherpabusinessconsultancy.com/wordpress/business-consultancy/353-revision-9.html', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(917, 2, '2010-10-13 15:15:47', '2010-10-13 15:15:47', 'Growing businesses present different challenges for the management team. With changing business dynamics and client''s spreading over wider geographies, productivity, motivation and communication become key to sucess. \r\n \r\nStructuring the key elements of the business and mile stones allows the right people to take ownership and drive within the organisation. Innovative ideas and solutions often come from the people that do the job. Capturing and using these ideas allow the business to flex and grow.', 'Improve Communication', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '134-revision-9', '', '', '2010-10-13 15:15:47', '2010-10-13 15:15:47', '', 134, 'http://www.sherpabusinessconsultancy.com/wordpress/business-consultancy/134-revision-9.html', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(918, 2, '2010-11-01 10:50:34', '2010-11-01 10:50:34', 'Growing businesses present different challenges for the management team. With changing business dynamics and client’s spreading over wider geographies, productivity, motivation and communication become key to success.\r\n\r\nEffective processes and team structure are essential to ensure that communication does not suffer as the business grows. Structuring key elements of the business to improve decision making processes allows the right people to take ownership and drive the organisation. \r\n\r\nTake time to look at the flow of communication in your business and establish structures and processes for maximum benefit. Innovative ideas and solutions often come from the people that do the job. Capturing and using these ideas allows the business to flex and grow.', 'Improve Communication', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '134-revision-10', '', '', '2010-11-01 10:50:34', '2010-11-01 10:50:34', '', 134, 'http://www.sherpabusinessconsultancy.com/wordpress/business-consultancy/134-revision-10.html', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
