(982, 2, '2010-11-01 09:39:01', '2010-11-01 09:39:01', 'Whether you''re a young start up, a growing business or a well established SME looking to conquer new markets, Sherpa can help you reach your goals. \r\n\r\ne have the knowledge and experience to take you to the next level. \r\n\r\n', 'Solutions', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '62-revision-33', '', '', '2010-11-01 09:39:01', '2010-11-01 09:39:01', '', 62, 'http://www.sherpabusinessconsultancy.com/wordpress/business-consultancy/62-revision-33.html', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(984, 2, '2010-11-01 12:04:07', '2010-11-01 12:04:07', 'Sherpa were approached by a leading third sector organisation who were seeking strategic guidance as they entered a period of economic uncertainty. \r\n\r\nThe organisation embarked on a organisational development project with Sherpa to build a cohesive action plan to deal with a reduced budget and a commitment to focus on their core providing adequate service provision to vulnerable users.\r\n\r\n<strong>Background:</strong> The management team had identified a need for change due to impending budgetary cuts and were looking to create greater accountability through more streamlined business processes.\r\n\r\nThey also recognized the need to restructure the management team and to return to a focus on ‘core business’ to ensure that the services provided to their clients were not impacted by restricted finances.\r\n\r\n<strong>The solution:</strong> A new management structure allowed the business to focus on what the organisation was originally created to provide. With greater control, the business was in a strong position to deal with financial issues as they arose. Reconfiguring the financial structure meant that the business could strategically plan to cope with budget cuts, and the outsourcing of non-service related roles to specialist providers created greater accountability and a return to core business.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n', 'Third sector', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '272-revision-11', '', '', '2010-11-01 12:04:07', '2010-11-01 12:04:07', '', 272, 'http://www.sherpabusinessconsultancy.com/wordpress/business-consultancy/272-revision-11.html', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(985, 2, '2010-10-15 14:57:04', '2010-10-15 14:57:04', 'Sherpa specialise in business growth. We work with entrepreneurs and management teams to realise the potential in your business. Our team of consultants and mentors deliver strategic and tactical support to create high performing businesses. ', 'Home', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '50-revision-19', '', '', '2010-10-15 14:57:04', '2010-10-15 14:57:04', '', 50, 'http://www.sherpabusinessconsultancy.com/wordpress/business-consultancy/50-revision-19.html', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(988, 2, '2010-11-01 16:03:19', '2010-11-01 16:03:19', 'Non executive directors are extremely useful for any business that wants to grow or change. If you feel you may be in a comfort zone with business and would like to challenge the status quo, a non executive is a great solution. Because they are not wrapped up in the day-to-day running of the business, a non executive director can often see risks and opportunities the the executive management may overlook. \r\n\r\nNon executive directors are valuable during periods of change or growth in a business to bring specialised knowledge in a particular area. Sherpa have worked with businesses through times of corporate transition such as funding cuts, raising finances  uch as:\r\nsales\r\nfinance\r\noperations\r\n\r\nA non executive brings personal qualities and skills to the management team that may not currently exist. They can mediate if there are clashes with strong, difficult or opinionated personalities or add drive, innovation and dynamism if this is what the company is lacking. A non executive director can also bring a wealth of valuable contacts and high level connections in key target markets to make vital introductions. \r\n\r\nSherpa''s non executive directors see things from a different perspective to the operational team and provide a vital strategic overview.\r\n', 'Non Executive Directors', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '153-revision-11', '', '', '2010-11-01 16:03:19', '2010-11-01 16:03:19', '', 153, 'http://www.sherpabusinessconsultancy.com/wordpress/business-consultancy/153-revision-11.html', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
